headlines.description: — If Jayson Tatum wants to argue with the referees during a 30-point blowout, that’s OK with Celtics coach Joe Mazzulla.
headlines.shortLinkText: Celtics light up Udoka, Rockets 145-113, improve to 19-0 in Boston

headlines.description: — Kyle Kuzma scored 29 points and the Washington Wizards took advantage of the Atlanta Hawks' worst offensive night this season to roll to a 127-99 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kuzma, Wizards roll to 127-99 win in Hawks' worst offensive performance of the season

events.name: New York Knicks at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 24 points and 11 rebounds, OG Anunoby scored 18 points and the New York Knicks defeated the makeshift Memphis Grizzlies 106-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Randle scores 24 to lead the Knicks over the short-handed Grizzlies 106-94

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 33 points and the Milwaukee Bucks used a big fourth quarter to pull away for a 129-118 victory over the short-handed Golden State Warriors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks have big fourth quarter, beat Warriors 129-118 with Curry resting

events.name: Orlando Magic at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Time after time, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander punished the Orlando Magic by making difficult shots while getting fouled.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat short-handed Magic 112-100 to tie Timberwolves for Western Conference lead

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Rookie Jordan Hawkins scored a season-high 34 points in his 11th start to lead seven New Orleans players in double figures as the Pelicans beat the Dallas Mavericks 118-108 on Saturday night in a game in which most of both teams’ regular starters...
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Hawkins scores 34 points to lead Pelicans past Mavericks 118-108

events.name: Chicago Bulls at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic had 24 points and 16 rebounds, and the Chicago Bulls overcame a career-high 30 points from Tre Jones to rally for a 122-116 victory Saturday over the San Antonio Spurs, who sat Victor Wembanyama.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vucevic's double-double helps Bulls rally past Jones, Spurs as Wembanyama watches, 122-116

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Lauri Markkanen had 29 points, nine rebounds and five assists to lead the Utah Jazz to a 132-123 victory over the Los Angeles Lakers on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz rally past Lakers 132-123, extending winning streak to five
